The paper deals with problems related to graph drawings, specifically orthogonal graph drawings. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and fixed-parameter tractability, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of inapproximability results suggests a connection to complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves optimization problems, which are often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the length of longest edge and total edge length, which are related to graph theory (cs.GT).
